<title type="html"><![CDATA[convert PAL to NTSC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4074&amp;p=33039#p33039"><![CDATA[
If no PAL adaption was done, the only thing you might want to do is check if it is region locked. Despite NTSC and PAL having different lock out chips, probably because of those piggyback/T-Connector adapters many games will check a register to find out if the system is NTSC or PAL and may refuse to run if there is a mismatch. <br /><br />A good way to find out is load the rom in SNES9x or ZSNES and use the "Force NTSC" option.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Sat Apr 26, 2008 12:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
